pr_body:
- [x] Port to Collabwrapper

- [x] Test collaboration

There are the things I tried while testing collaboration -

- joiner is able to join the sharer.
- Clicking on Start a new game by sharer , starts a new game at joiner. Also only sharer is able to start a new game, joiner cannot.
- Same grid is shared between sharer and joiner ( same colours also).
- If joiner recognises a pattern and clicks on True or False buttons , game state will be updated in sharer and vice-versa.
- Explore some examples is not shared between sharer and joiner.

There are 10 levels. Game will start from 1st level , if you give 5 correct answers, you will be updated to next level. These are the patterns for each level.

- Level 1: Center dot is Red
- Level 2: Monochrome
- Level 3: Max chroma
- Level 4: lighter as it moves up
- Level 5: chroma increases to center
- Level 5: diagonal is True
- Level 6: equiluminent
- Level 7: complementary
- Level 8: hue increase down
- Level 9: interlocking hues
- Level 10: checkerboard

Collaboration test is successful. Please review and merge. @quozl @chimosky .

pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 407079584, 'comment_body': "I don't think you should add W503. It hasn't been added in other activities and can you explain why ignore warning W503 than fix it?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 11, 15, 56, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'JuiP', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 407156656, 'comment_body': "No there is no way to fix the error. We have to put line break before or after a binary operator otherwise it would end up with another error E501: line too long(82 > 79). If we put line break after binary operator , it will give W504 and if we put line break before , it will give W503. As according to new code style of Knuth's, W503 is recommended before W504. You can have a look at doc-https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0008/#should-a-line-break-before-or-after-a-binary-operator. Thanks", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 4, 12, 7, 1, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Saumya-Mishra9129', 'type': 'User'}]
